---
description: Use these rules whenever you create or edit UI tests
alwaysApply: false
---

- Playwright MCP is available for browser automation and inspection
- Frontend is running on `FRONTEND_URL` from `config/constants.ts`
- Always use `data-testid` based selectors (e.g., `page.getByTestId('login-submit-button')`)
- Once you complete a test, run the tests to verify they work as expected. In case of application bugs let me know about it.
- Do not generate too many tests for input validation (frontend validation). Make it 1-3 tests max. Assume sufficient test coverage on unit test level.
- Make sure that `npm run lint` passes after each incremental change. 
- Use // given (test setup), // when (tested action), // then (test verification) comments to structure the tests.
- Use Faker to generate random data for the tests.
- Use API clients defined in the `http` folder to generate data for the tests.
- ALWAYS explore the application via Playwright MCP to find out `test-testid` selectors and to build understanding of how the application works.

## Shared Test Helpers

Use reusable helpers from `tests/helpers/` for common operations:

### Product Helpers (`tests/helpers/productHelper.ts`)
### Cart Helpers (`tests/helpers/cartHelper.ts`)
### Order Helpers (`tests/helpers/orderHelper.ts`)

Add new helpers if necessary.

## Page Object Model (POM)

- Use Page Object Model pattern for UI tests
- Page classes are located in `/pages` folder
- Reusable components are located in `/pages/components` folder
- Use composition (not inheritance) to include components in page classes
- Example: `LoginPage` has `toast: Toast` and `header: LoggedOutHeader` as properties

## File Organization

- Page classes: `/pages/{PageName}Page.ts`
- Component classes: `/pages/components/{ComponentName}.ts`
- UI test files: `/tests/ui/{feature}.ui.spec.ts`
- Shared helpers: `/tests/helpers/` (shared between API and UI tests)

## Key Principles
- ALWAYS use shared helpers for common test setup patterns
- NEVER duplicate helper functions - add new helpers to `tests/helpers/` instead
- Use custom fixtures when a test suite needs consistent setup (e.g., `productsUiFixture.ts`)
